        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-05T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.01/7–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 502<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HK1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-05T21:00:00+03:00">July 5, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2419. I delivered this evening to the Polish <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>
                    the texts of the President’s message to <persName corresp="#p_OEB1">Osóbka-Morawski</persName> and of the public statement re the recognition
                    of the Polish Provisional Govt of National Unity (<gloss target="#t_reDeptel1">ReDeptel</gloss> 1505, July 3, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d502fn1">Not
                        printed. For the texts referred to, see <ref target="#d496">documents Nos.
                            496</ref> and <ref target="#d501">501</ref>.</note>) the Polish <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> expressed his appreciation for being provided
                    with these texts and stated that he would <pb facs="0868" n="736" xml:id="pg_736"/> transmit them to his govt immediately and that the
                    announcement of recognition would appear in tomorrow’s morning papers in
                    Poland.</p>
                <p>The Brit <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> is also sending a communication to
                    the Polish <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> this evening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
